inn1.comm: round the wicket, slip in place, Smith goes onto the back foot and drives to cover
dragged down short, pulled firmly out to deep midwicket...goes one bounce as it skims out to the fielder
short again, this one skids on and Powell is camped on the back foot but manages to flick it through the leg side
touch more air this time, fuller, pitches outside leg and defended
goes back and tucks to square leg
full at the stumps, pushed down the ground to long-on. Gentle start.
back of a length outside off, pushed into the off side and he sets off for a single before being sent back
nice delivery, shapes away from the right hander and beats the outside edge as Smith fishes for it
short of a length, and this time it's a lovely piece of timing off the back foot square of the wicket through point. Stokes chases hard and just manages to flick it back. Good work.
on off stump, 138kph/85mph, defended on the back foot to mid-off
huge appeal for lbw! Nips back into Powell from quite a full length. Given not out. Broad likes, as ever. But he resists the urge to review. May have pitched outside leg. Yep, well outside leg
too short this time, outside off, nicely driven off the back foot square through point
and he strikes! What a soft dismissal. Full outside leg, Smith tries to turn it through the leg side and just ends up clipping a low catch to short midwicket
pushed off the back foot to cover
full on leg stump, presses forward and defends to leg
dropped at leg slip! Was outside leg stump, Edwards glanced it around the corner and Bresnan couldn't hang on to his right. He was moving to his left, so his weight was on the wrong foot
full, comes forward and drives down the ground
fired in full at the stumps, driven up to mid-off
full on middle, Powell keen to stay back as he defends to mid-on
outside off, Powell defends square to point
cracking delivery, 138kph/85mph, short of a length outside off and climbs past Powell's outside edge...bounce and a hint of swing
short of a length, punched off the back foot to cover
lovely shot, textbook perfect as he steps into a full delivery outside off and drives between cover and mid-off. Holds the pose. It's worth a picture or two.
on leg stump, tucked off the pads to square leg
round the wicket, on leg stump, worked out to midwicket
flicks his wrists as he whips this from outside leg to square leg
comes forward, opens the face and the ball runs past short third man
defended to the leg side
shuffles down the pitch then pushes down to long-on
driven down the ground
starts with a juicy full toss which is driven through the off side to the right of long-off
worked off the stumps to square leg
tossed up, plenty of air, Edwards comes down the pitch but ends up yorking himself
defended to the on side
slightly shorter, punched off the back foot and can't beat midwicket and the bowler
full on middle and off, stretches forward to defend. Half an appeal for lbw but just a polite enquiry really (bit like our show with George and Crofty)
defended from off stump to cover
goes back, the ball slides on, worked down to mid-on
comes down the pitch a couple of steps then drives to long-off
on off stump, blocked to the off side
some aggression from Edwards as he uses his feet then drills this towards mid-off who can't quite stop it cleanly
defended square into the off side, sharp running and good awareness to take the single
nicely driven down the ground, used his feet to get to the pitch
gets across his stumps, glances it past leg slip but it wasn't a catch this time
pushed across outside off, played firmly just to the left of mid-off
full at the stumps, uses his wrists and this is neat batting picking up another single to mid-on
takes this from outside off with a flick of his bottom hand, down to long-on
another soft catch! On leg stump, Powell aiming to work it into the leg side and gets a gentle leading edge back to Moeen who moves a step to his left to take it
full on leg stump, flicked to square leg

what a catch! That's a ripper from Tredwell at slip. The ball slid across outside off, Edwards was aiming to force it through the off side. It was a thick edge and Tredwell stuck out his right hand to snaffle the ball when it was almost behind him
patted gently into the off side
touch shorter on leg stump, defended
worked off the pads through square leg and deep midwicket can't prevent the second
fuller at the stumps, pushed up to mid-off for a quick single
tries to work this into the leg side but gets taken high on the pads
that's a well-controlled sweep, he went down early and took the ball off straight. Rolled his wrists to keep the ball down.
flicked off the pads to square leg
again finds the man at square leg
comes forward, defended off a thick inside edge to the leg side
beats the outside edge with one that slides on with the arm, nicely bowled by Moeen
round the wicket, full on off, defended
comes across to off stump, works slightly across the line as he defends to the leg side
forward and defended to cover
full outside off, hint of drift, defended on the front foot
more air this time, hangs there for a little while, drops on a full length and is prodded square into the off side
drifts in from outside off, played with soft hands to gully...very accurate start from Tredwell
round the wicket, on leg stump, comes off a thick inside edge to short fine leg
full on off stump, whipped to mid-on with plenty of bottom hand
full outside off, dug out and beats short midwicket down to long-on
nicely bowled, pulls the length back a touch, on off stump and Simmons is reaching for it a little and the ball runs off a thick outside edge
onto the back foot and pushed back to the bowler
angled onto leg stump, flicked out to deep square. Parry will feel a little more relaxed after that. He landed all six deliveries
full outside off, prodded back down the pitch
uses his feet then drives with quite a flourish to mid-on
down the pitch again, this time he lofts it over long-on but doesn't quite get the distance...the ball clears Broad running back then plugs on the outfield
touch short outside off but it doesn't cost him as he drives to cover
back on a full length at middle and off, Bravo forward and defends
gets a small stride forward and blocks
comes forward, opens the face as he drives to try and find a gap in the off side
tossed up full at his feet, driven to extra cover
a little flatter this time, defended
straighter delivery, Simmons pushes towards mid-on who is deep enough to allow the single
down the track again, drives in the air and it goes one bounce to long-on...Bravo keen to change the tempo
this time the drive is along the ground to long-off
full on off stump, comes forward and defends to point
a moment of relief for the batsmen, Tredwell drags it down short, Simmons goes onto the back foot and cracks it through the covers. Just has the legs to beat the chaser
over the wicket, short again, poor delivery which sits up and allows him to drive off the back foot through the covers
that's a big 'un! He's been trying to do this for a few overs, uses his feet and this time strikes cleanly through the line and sends it into the stands over long-on
flatter at off stump, defended
pushed into the covers
too short from Parry this time, Simmons cuts it hard through point as the momentum builds for West Indies
fuller on off stump, defended back down the pitch
pushed back to the bowler
angled in to middle and leg, blocked into midwicket
short again, on off stump, but this time he finds cover off the back foot
goes onto the back foot and turns it to midwicket
tossed up onto middle and leg, forward and tucked to midwicket
swept from outside leg stump, misses, it cannons off Buttlers pads and runs away to square leg
over the wicket, floated up just outside off, tucked to midwicket
fuller and pushed down to long-on
back around, a touch short and cut out to deep cover
floated up, forward and Simmons gets a thick inside edge from some turn into vacant square leg
forward on the stumps and blocked up the wicket
forward just outside off to push into the covers
touch short, played off the back foot to extra cover
back again, pushes to cover again
forward trying to steer it into a gap on the off side, no run to backward point
tighter line, forward played back to the bowler
back and pushed up to the bowler, very tidy six
forward on middle and leg to play into midwicket
forward on off stump, pushed into the covers, too close to the fielder
similar delivery, dead-batted this time
played to leg, gets struck on the pad, it was sliding down, runs wide of short long leg
arm ball slides past the outside edge, beats the bat
forward just outside off, blocking into the covers, another very tidy six
short of a length, played to mid-on off the back foot
forward on off stump, clipping down to long-on, Simmons now just in a cap
over the wicket, tossed up on middle and leg, worked to midwicket
down the track, not quite to the pitch, blocked back to the bowler
quicker ball nearly has Bravo caught out but he forces to cover
down again, again can only block it back to the bowler
full delivery a foot wide of off stump, driven at rather loosely, gets a thick inside edge to midwicket
tighter line, again full, this driven more compactly to mid-off
bumper slides down the leg side
full and straight, driven back to Broad's right hand, smart stop
full length once more, this just blocked from off stump back to the bowler
short, Simmons goes to pull and gets a bottom edge into his thigh that runs nowhere
short again, a foot outside off, Simmons opens the face and guides it down to third man
full and straight, little bit of angle to work with so Simmons whips it wide of deep midwicket for a dashing couple
better length, this just pushed to midwicket
shot! A step down the wicket and pans a length ball over mid-on, top strike and it very nearly lands on the rope, flat and fast that went, great timing
similar delivery, this a touch wider of off stump and just pushed up to cover
slower ball strikes the pad with Simmons looking to play to cover
another slower ball, this fuller and it's driven inside mid-on for a quick single
strays in line and gets clipped out to long leg
short ball that Bravo is late on pulling and chips it just wide of Broad's left hand and well short of mid-on
around the wicket, full on off stump, driven to cover

length delivery just outside off, Bravo goes back to try and cut it and gets a bottom edge into off stump ending a slightly tortured innings. Rocking back to try and guide away a delivery much too full for a cut, Bravo has got a thick bottom edge that has bounced and flicked the top of off stump
back of a length at the body, tucked up on the leg side
bumper outside off, swayed inside
full at the stumps, flicked to midwicket where there's a smart save diving low to the fielder's right
short and pulled nicely, controlled stroke keeping it down and gets it out to deep square leg
another pull, this from a higher mark but controlled again and gets it in the gap between long leg and deep square, nicely fielded
full just outside off, a firm punch to extra cover
slower ball, patted up on the on side
similar delivery, blocked again coming forward
full at the off stump, played forward and ran back to the bowler
again full, flicked to midwicket from the stumps

bumper and Bravo gets it all wrong and takes a might whack on the side of the head, that is nasty, made a horrible sound and Bravo is immediately on the floor, Broad checks if he's okay and on comes the physio. He turned his head away and took it half on the side of the grille and half on the neck
Broad sends down another short ball, Bravo gets on top of this and angles it to point and they dash through for a sharp single

full and driven back to the bowler, Broad parried it and they decided to run on the rebound. Had Moeen Ali, coming across the wicket and flicking the ball back out of the side of his hand, hit the stumps, Simmons would have been well gone
back of a length outside off, stays inside the line
forward on off stump, dropped to point and they take a quick run
full on middle and leg, flicked in the air but safely short of long leg
full and driven wide of mid-off, they take a quick single, there's a direct hit and they'll check but Simmons is safely home
slower ball, batsman plays to leg and gets struck on the pad, appeal for lbw, not out given and it was high
bumper, pulled in the air but bouncing short of long leg
another slower ball on the stumps, flicked wide of mid-on and they take a sharp single
forward on off stump blocking to backward point
straight delivery blocked back to the bowler
short and pulled wide of deep square but just for a single
back full around around off stump, blocked in the crease
sharp bouncer and Simmons pulls out of the hook he was lining up
wide of off stump, driven hard and beats point but not the sweeper
full at the off stump, pushed up to short extra
full at the off stump, driven off the inner half of the bat back to the bowler
a step across the stumps but just a funny poke that gets a thick outside edge which chips almost to backward point, it runs past the fielder for a couple
full on leg stump, flicked behind square and deep midwicket, Root, has a long chase and makes a fine diving save
full just outside off, pushed to short extra
touch wide and cut hard to Stokes who takes off to his left at backward point for a fine save
full just outside off into the covers
straighter line and blocked up the wicket
down the wicket and works this through midwicket
forward just outside off to dab through the covers
played around it slightly and find short long leg who dives and fumbles so they get a second run
full on off stump, pushed with an open face to extra cover
full just outside off pushed to short extra cover
this angles in at the pads and hurries Simmons, beating the inside edge, it was going miles down leg for the lbw
flashing drive from the crease to backward point
full delivery, a lovely straight drive will be cut off from long-on running to his left
another flashing drive and this finds deep cover
full at the off stump, driven to mid-off
round the wicket, worked away from off stump to square cover
touch short outside off but Simmons misses his cut shot
fuller this time, gets onto the front foot and drives to cover
placed square into the off side
push and run into the covers
escapes with a slightly short delivery outside off as it gets cut straight to point
pushed down the leg side, starts with a wide
gets onto off stump, a full length, defended to cover
powerful drive and he beats mid-off, was very full from Stokes and Bravo put all his power behind the shot. The bat turned in his hand, so not perfectly time but hit it hard enough
slanted into the pads, deflects behind square and the lack of pace on the ball means they can make a second
banged in short, he goes for the pull and that comes off his ribs towards Buttler. He's in a bit of pain after that
fuller on off stump, defended
keeps it full at middle, met with a straight bat and it's punched firmly towards mid-on
just out of Tredwell's reach, he got a leading edge trying to work a full ball to leg but it was chipped over the outstretched hand
worked down the ground
uses his feet then works this from outside leg along the ground through midwicket
touch short outside off, spins back into Simmons as he cuts through point to the cover sweeper
fuller outside off, Simmons comes forward with bat and pad together
gets across outside off, works the ball to long-on to bring up back-to-back half-centuries. Another well-controlled innings after the team had been in trouble
back of a length on off stump, opens the face and places it out to deep cover
full and powerfully driven straight to mid-off...but a wayward throw gives away a single. Sloppy.
opens the face and runs the ball to third man
shoved way down the leg side, another wide
full outside off, gets forward and pushes out to deep cover
even fuller this time, driven firmly through the off side
short ball, at the body, he goes for the pull and isn't far from picking out deep square-leg
round the wicket, full, flicked to midwicket
driven back to the bowler this time
glances off the pad fine of the keeper, for some reason Tredwell appeals but that must have pitched outside leg
fantastic shot! Was given a touch more air by Tredwell and Simmons responded by going inside out over extra cover, just opened the face at the last moment. Lovely.
now he drops a single into the off side. Mature batting

stumped down the leg side! But only just. Buttler will breath a sigh if relief here, because he so nearly messed it up. Bravo was miles out of his ground, but Buttler lost control of the ball but the third umpire has ruled that it was still the ball (and not the gloves) which broke the stumps. The ball wasn't called wide
round the wicket, tucked through midwicket
on off stump, Sammy comes forward and defends
goes back to a shorter ball, almost early on his shot as the ball stops in the surface but is able to work it into midwicket
dragged down short but it's just nudged along the ground to deep midwicket
full at middle, hint of turn, defended
blocked back to the bowler. Good comeback over by Parry
on leg stump, flicked down to fine leg
short of a length at the body, gets inside the line and works it off his hip to fine leg
on off stump, short of a length, played to cover
short ball, Simmons goes for the pull and it comes off a top edge near the splice but doesn't have the carry to reach deep midwicket
bouncer over off stump, Sammy ducks
short again, outside off, loops through to Buttler and doesn't actually carry on the full
floated full outside off, prodded to the covers
uses his feet, but the ball is shorter so he has to adjust and plays it square to point
comes down again, Parry keeping it back of a length, defended
that's a good connection...a slightly fuller delivery, he stayed in the crease, went down for the slog sweep and launched it high over deep midwicket

first wicket for Parry! Good response. He held his nerve. Simmons trying to go over the top again, but didn't seem quite so committed this time. It was more a chip as he came down the pitch and it lands in the hands of deep midwicket.
full on off stump, Sammy leans forward to defend
top shot, a floaty full delivery outside off and Ramdin leans forward to drive through the off side
drags the length back, defended square to point
bouncer over off stump, Ramdin ducks
squares him up a touch on off stump, defended to the covers
on off stump, defended
a beauty! On a full length and nips away to beat the outside edge
full and pushed to long off
on the back foot, defended
swept off the stumps out to deep square
onto the back foot and flat-bats to midwicket
worked out to midwicket
touch fuller, he comes forward and pushes back to Parry. Tight over.
full at the off stump, blocked back to the bowler

length ball angles back from a length, Ramdin is late on this and guides it onto his stumps and now West Indies are really struggling. Ramdin stood in the crease and looked to run a length ball down to third man but it came back at him, cramped him for room and he ended up deflecting it into his timbers
full at the off stump, flicked back to the bowler
length delivery around off stump, blocked into the covers from the crease
bumper, ducked beneath
full again and blocked firmly up to mid-off

back of a length delivery, Sammy goes back and pulls hard to midwicket, Broad reaches up to take the catch or does he? He spills it, turns around, flicks the ball up and then is able to cling on. Sammy peels himself off having picked out the fielder, he connected very well but couldn't find the gap
forward and blocked in front of off stump
played forward and blocked back to the bowler again
props forward to defend again
down the track and hammered hard over mid-off, great timing

shuffle down the crease, aims another swing down the ground, misses and Buttler whips off the bails no doubt about this one at all. There wasn't the flight on this delivery that made is as attractive to attack and it has zipped past Narine's bat and he actually held the pose in the follow-through knowing he was a goner
short ball outside off, ignored
short again, Miller sways inside the line again
fuller a foot wide of off stump, Miller shoulders arms
tighter line and blocked on the front foot
bumper and ducked
full at the stumps, Miller tries to clear the front leg and swing over the leg side but is hurried and gets it off high on the bat to midwicket
full at the stumps, flicked to midwicket
too straight and it turns down the leg side
a foot outside off stump, tucked off the back foot to cover
aims a strike over the leg side, mistimed and it chips in front of deep midwicket
full and blocked back to the bowler
wider outside off, tries to late cut and gets it off a bottom edge on the bounce to slip
little straight and tickled fine, chase for deep-backward square
around the wicket, straight line, blocked into the covers

down the track and lifted down the ground but Rampaul doesn't get all of it and long-off takes the catch running to his left. Seemed to come off low on the bat and the fielder was able to run a few yards to his left and pouch the chance a yard inside the boundary

inn2.comm: full outside off, left alone
full delivery, on the pads, and it's clipped very sweetly but straight to mid-on
England up and running, drives a delivery outside off and it comes off a thick outside edge which beats gully and runs to vacant third man area
full on off stump, hints to come back into Lumb who defends
finds the edge, but it's a slower ball and played with soft hands so falls well short of slip
length delivery, tucked to midwicket
full on middle, hint of swing into Moeen who clips it through the leg side
nearly chops on, it's back of a length and he aims to angle it down to third man but it comes off the bottom edge into his boot
short and fairly wide, 124kph/77mph, left alone
shuffles across the crease and flicks this from around middle and off through straight midwicket
full outside off, left alone
he goes after some width but it takes the cue end of the bat into the off side
another batsmen gets taken on the helmet, a slippery bouncer from Bravo and it beats him for pace then glances off the back of his head down to third man
pushed across full outside off, left alone
leaves alone again
on off stump, flicked to mid-on
comes onto the front foot and drives back to the bowler
lovely stroke, goes after a wide delivery this time with a lofted cover drive. No holding back, placed it perfectly. A very languid shot
big appeal for caught behind, but more from behind the batsman. The delivery nipped back off a length and cut Lumb in half. Rampaul just had his hands on his head. Clipped to top of the back leg.
defended into the off side
now Lumb goes after a wide delivery, threw the kitchen sink at that, his weight was on the back foot and the ball flew off a thick top edge down to third man...just wide of Sammy at gully
short and wide, but Moeen misses out as he mistimes into the covers
short on leg stump, he pulls although is a little cramped for room and it comes high off the bat, although the lack of timing helps him come back for a second
a full-on bouncer this time, over leg stump, Moeen bails out of an attacking stroke and lets his pass over his shoulder
short outside off, Lumb thinks about pulling but then drops his bat and leaves alone
he helps this short ball around the corner on the leg side, rolled his wrists to ensure the ball went to ground although it still carried a fair distance in the air
short again, over leg stump (or perhaps just outside), Moeen goes to pull but the ball goes over his gloves
an elegant pull, played off one leg, and played with a lot of control out to deep square
keeps it short, pulled behind square on the leg side but deep square is just able to prevent the boundary
ah, a fuller delivery, on leg stump and it's clipped to deep square
outside off, hint of spin away, left alone
defended to the off side
fuller, he comes forward and drives down to long-off
gets a stride forward and defends with a slightly open face
think that was the other one, spinning into Moeen, finds a think inside edge but goes to ground past short leg
he's beaten in the flight here, but goes through his drive strongly enough that it clears the off-side ring
on off stump, defended on the back foot
aims to work this away from middle stump, a slower cutter, the ball runs to mid-on
a short-arm pull through square leg, dropped short again and Lumb has plenty of time
on off stump, short of a length, punched off the back foot to the left of cover

well, the short ball works! Moeen didn't keep this one down, and was hitting into the wind which is pretty strong, and provides deep square with a simple catch. Disappointing shot from Moeen, finding a deep fielder twice in two innings
another blow from a short ball, Wright goes for the pull and gets beaten. The ball hammers into his grille.
defended square to point
flicks a straight delivery out to deep midwicket
close! Almost beaten on the back foot as he plays into the off side against an offspinner
this one spins away, and bounces, to beat the top edge as he goes to cut
a beauty! Beats him all ends up. Grips and spins just enough to go past the outside edge. Not sure Wright has a clue
all over! That was on the cards. Wonderful over, but Wright out-classed. This scoots past the outside edge, the legspinner, and takes off stump
full on middle, nicely clipped away through midwicket
short of a length outside off, played down in front of the man at about fourth slip
left alone outside off
width outside off, chopped behind point down to third man
on middle and off, defended to the leg side
top shot! Terrific piece of timing on a slow pitch, punching a short-of-a-length delivery off the back foot through cover
gets forward and defends
beats the outside edge, bounce this time as well
fraction shorter and straighter, allows him to go back and tuck into square leg
prods forward on middle, defends to the leg side
a careful prod forward, pushed to the covers
quicker delivery outside off, left alone
round the wicket, full on leg stump, worked off his toes into midwicket
over the wicket, clipped straight into short leg
nice spin out of the footmarks, bounces at Lumb as he gets forward
defended to the off side
dragged down short, flicked off the back foot behind square
full from round the wicket, driven down to long-off
defended on the back foot
gets a think inside edge into his pads as tries to work into the leg side
playing back and then further back...another inside edge gets trapped between his legs
touch shorter, on off stump, defended to point
picks it off into midwicket, that seems to be their one release shot
strangled appeal for lbw, pitched outside leg...Lumb was aiming to work it through the leg side
driven off the back foot to cover
fuller delivery, stretches forward and plays square into the off side
a punchy drive to short cover
skids on a touch although Root was caught on the back foot
tight! Drifted on leg stump, Root tickled it to short fine-leg, Lumb called for the run but had to get the dive out. The fielder, perhaps, a little slow
shorter delivery outside off, turning into him, driven off the back foot down the ground
he misses out here, short and wide, but it's called wide anyway
full on off stump, driven to mid-off
round the wicket, touch shorter, driven square off the back foot through point
offers to spin away, played off the back foot to cover
straight delivery, pushed to cover
spins into Root, worked off the back foot through midwicket
round the wicket, outside off, left alone...half Narine's overs finished
short delivery, pulled from a kneeling position out to deep square
flicked from outside off to square leg
pushed square into the off side...fifty up for England
round the wicket, he plays this quite late and guides it to point...good running
drifts down the leg side, Lumb tickles it off his pads and it has the pace to reach the fine-leg boundary
worked out to midwicket
forward blocking in front of off stump
back and pushing up the wicket back to the bowler
full outside off, driven to cover
leg stump line, tucked past leg slip, it wasn't a chance, and it skips all the way to the fine leg fence
a little straight again and Root able to tuck easily out to deep midwicket
forward just outside off, runs this to backward point
around the wicket, forward comes Root on off stump to block with an open face to cover
waits for this to come to him a bit more and steers it into the gap wide of cover for a quick single
fails to adjust to the left hander and gets tucked wide of short long leg
too short and Root is back quickly to cut from off stump for four past cover, nice shot
back again and pushing to cover
forward this time dropping this into cover
length ball angled in and strikes the thigh pad
fuller outside off and struck nicely away wide of mid-on, decent timing, a fine save running back and diving in front of the rope
full again, flicked to mid-on
touch shorter and Root has more to work with flicking this wide of mid-on for a single
full and slides down leg
full length, pushed back to the bowler from just outside off
driven without timing to mid-on
goes to sweep and gets struck on the pad outside leg stump
fuller and driven up to mid-off
touch wider line and finds short extra this time
shimmy up the wicket and push to mid-on whom they take on and get home very comfortably
tossed up on off stump and rolled into the covers
flatter ball, flicked to short midwicket from just outside off stump
short and pulled easily down to long leg
slower ball driven outside off, slightly aerial but in the gap wide of cover and they get back for three
full but well wide of off stump, too wide in fact
full length on off stump, Root waits for it and drops it in front of point for a sharp single
tight off stump line, blocked on the front foot
slower ball very full outside off, Lumb rolls it down the ground and they run hard for two but refuse coming back
full just outside off and ran to point
forward just outside off, some turn and strikes the pad well outside the line of off stump
fuller and flicked with the turn to midwicket

quicker delivery, Lumb plays across it and misses, struck bang in front and plumb lbw the one pushed through works for Miller. Trying to play with the turn again, Lumb got right across his stumps but he was deceived by the extra pace and missed attempting to turn the ball to leg
forward just outside off and dropped into the covers
back this time and pushing into the covers
touch short and clipped through midwicket for an easy couple

full length delivery, Root comes forward and presses it back up the wicket, in fact he's popped it back to Bravo who takes a straightforward chance going to his right at waist height. Little bit of pace off the ball perhaps? It didn't seem that way but Root was on the stroke much too soon and tapped a catch back to the bowler

short first ball, well-directed right at the body, Buttler goes to avoid it but can't get his hands inside the line in time and gets a feather through to Ramdin and now this really is game on. Buttler got into a position to ride the bounce and try and drop it down, then saw it rising steeply and tried to get inside the line and failed, the ball brushing the glove through to Ramdin, West Indies are cock-a-hoop
another bumper and Bopara shows Buttler how it's done by getting under it quickly
full length on off stump, forward comes Bopara to knock it into the covers
short again, this outside off and easily ignored
full on the same line, ignored
floated up just outside off, flicked firmly down to long-on
dropped on the crease towards point
forward on the stumps, blocked again
back and playing to extra cover
leg stump, flicked around the corner, they take on short long leg and get home
flat delivery blocked in the crease
full just outside off, driven out to deep cover
around the wicket, Stokes uses the angle to flick out to deep square leg
full at the off stump, Bopara is blocking in the crease
overpitched and Bopara ease the tension with a lovely cover drive, opening the face to steer it past extra cover
back on a length, Bopara tries to dab it down for a single into the off side but slip is up quickly
full at the stumps, this is tucked up to mid-on
forward just outside off to knock this back to the bowler
forward on off stump, knocked into the on side

tries to turn this to leg, it cannons high up off the pad and provides an easy catch to Ramdin but the umpires gives it not out. Hold on, Stokes is off! He's turned and is trudging back to the pavilion! Quite remarkable! Stokes gives himself out. It's not immediately obvious on the replay that he got any edge onto his pad there but obviously Stokes knew and fair play to him
forward on the stump and patted back up the wicket
forward just outside off and played back to the bowler
forward blocking again
forward just outside off and blocked back to the bowler
full at the stumps and driven smartly to mid-on
slower ball on off stump, Bopara forward running it back to the bowler
short outside off, Bopara lets it go through
fuller on the same line, Bopara shoulders arms
touch tighter line and Bopara drives it out to the deep cover for a single
forward on the stumps, running this back to the bowler
turned around the corner to a straighter fuller ball
forward on the stumps just blocking this
forward on the stumps and played back to the bowler
slightly overpitched and Bresnan drives it to the left of mid-off for a quick single
off stump line, blocked in the crease
doosra first up, blocked very hurried in the crease in front of middle and off
another doosra, it turns away from off stump and Bresnan shoulders arms, picked that one I think
doosra #3, Bresnan blocks it just outside off stump into the covers
fuller, this also goes the other way, Bresnan spotted it and shouldered arms again
straighter line, blocked in the crease
fired down the leg side, a precious couple of extras as it cannons of Randin's pad
a foot outside off, Bopara follows it, it was another doosra, and beat the outside edge
floated up on the stumps, pushed back to the bowler
straighter line, tickled into midwicket
back of a length on middle and leg, Bresnan jumps inside the line and clips it through square leg
full a foot outside off, pushed gently through the covers
forward on off stump and ran back to the bowler
dragged down a little and pulled wide of deep midwicket for a couple
full on the stumps, flicked wide of mid-on for a quick single
short ball just outside off, Bresnan followed it and there's a loud cry for caught behind, not out given, Bresnan stands his ground!
slashed at outside off and misses, touch too full to try and cut
tighter line and this time Bresnan leaves alone
tighter line again, Bresnan tries to pull this and misses
finally connects, cutting out to deep cover and brings the hundred up with a single to deep cover
nearly strikes first ball, Bresnan going for a pull and the ball creeps over middle stump
full on off stump, no width, defended
comes forward to a full delivery, gets a thick inside edge into his boot
touch shorter, punched to cover
can't get anything away at the moment, driven to cover
short of a length, played off the back foot towards long-on so he'll keep the strike
positive stroke, full at the stumps and he punches it straight of mid-on...it doesn't look like it will make the boundary, but it's not a great chase by Powell
outside off, left alone
back of a length, on off stump, defended to cover

a shambles from England! Superb fielding. Bresnan flicked it strongly off his toes, he thought it was past Dwayne Bravo at wide mid-on but he's a wonderful fielder. He dived, picked up the ball then returned it to the keeper with Bresnan well short.
short of a length at the hip, tucked to short fine leg or is almost a leg gully

sharp bouncer, and given! But Broad has reviewed. Bang in, took Broad by surprise. Hard to tell what it touched on the first replay. Has to be conclusive because it's been given. No Hot Spot in this series. From front on it appears to have missed the glove. And it's overturned.
outside off, slower ball, dabbed to short third man
full at the stumps, tucked out to long-on where two fielders get into a tangle
short, outside off, cut in the air but well clear of point down to third man
punched out to cover
finds the gap this time, a lovely piece of timing square of the wicket off the back foot. Pierced the gap between point and cover
a fill delivery, another slower one at 104kph/64mph, which is punched down to long-on
flash and a miss outside off, trying to cut
slower ball outside off, drops into space square into the off side
full at the stumps, defended to mid-off
close! Nearly finds fine leg. A short ball, Broad goes for the pull and it flies off a top edge down to fine leg where Edwards can't quite get underneath it
short of a length, his feet are off the ground as he defends this square

dropped! And this one is a clear life. Broad flashing at a delivery outside off, going for a square cut, the edge flies to Dwayne Bravo's left at slip but he can't hold on despite getting two hands to it with a good dive. You'd back him to catch that
round the wicket, full at off stump, driven to cover
short, angled into him, pulled out to deep square and managed to keep the ball down this time
cracking shot...Bopara picks the slower ball, it's full outside off, and he drives it beautifully wide of mid-off. He can, at times, look so classy
short of a length, driven into the covers followed by a loud scream of 'no'
this one tails back into Bopara from outside off, it guides it down to third man

almost another catch! And is this a misjudgement on the boundary by Powell? Broad went for the pull to another short ball, he was hitting into the wind, Powell seemed to have come in too far because the ball bounced over him and was still just four
pushes forward to a full ball outside off, places it neatly into the off side...West Indies won't mind getting Broad on strike
goes down early to sweep, it spins across him outside off. Ramdin can't glove it cleanly
full at off stump, pushed down the ground to long-off
this one spins away, played off the back foot square into the off side
beats the outside edge although Broad did well not to follow it
and again, pushed across the left hander but it's just a dot ball. England did well in that over.
full at the stumps, tries to work it to the leg side but only gets it back to the bowler
full outside off, Bopara comes forward and drives to cover
beaten by a short ball, he thought it was there for a square drive. It probably was.
precious runs, another controlled stroke by Bopara as he takes advantage of some width and cuts behind square down to an empty third man
fuller again, comes forward and it comes off a thick inner part of the bat to the leg side...Rampaul scampers across to midwicket
nicely timed off the back foot, stands tall and punches a back-of-a-length delivery far enough to left of cover to allow single
driven behind square, beats a diving point to third man
full outside off, leans forward and pushes another quick single which went almost straight to cover. Good job Broad has long strides
round the wicket, short of a length, runs off an open face to third man
slower ball, very full, dug out and Bravo races across to field
it's another slow ball and this time it's not quite so full and Bopara is able to get under it enough to drive it over Bravo's head...maybe he didn't mean it to go so straight
defended to the off side
short on leg stump, Broad jumps into a defensive push and manages to squeeze a single to point
sweet drive, but picks out cover
on a length outside off, angles this down to third man
short on leg stump, he hops into a defensive prod to the leg side
short again, Broad staying leg-side of the ball as he defends to the off side...Broad screaming at Bopara to get back in his crease
another short one, Broad rides it well, it runs off a thick edge and looks like it will evade slip but Sammy dives
very full, prodding square towards backward point who can't stop the single. The throw is wayward, but no extras
slides past the outside edge as he lunges forward...getting a big stride in
comes round the wicket, makes him play, defended to point
tries to work it into an off-side gap, but runs to point
lovely delivery, spinning away to beat Broad. But it's a dot ball.
edged! But it goes to ground and bisects slip and gully. What a bonus of a boundary that is for England and they survive another Narine over
short of a length, opens the face and glides down to third man
over the wicket, full outside off, Broad hammers a drive through the covers...the sweeper scampers around the boundary
excellent bouncer, over middle and leg, and equally well played by Broad as he drops his hands and sways out of line (for a moment, a little of the old Caribbean feel)
gives himself a touch of room by staying on leg stump, it's back of a length around off and he drives strongly behind point. Third man can't stop the two
back of a length, cut firmly again but this time Smith dives to save at point
beats him with his last delivery, another short one which Broad tries to get through the off side but it bounces over his bat
watches this like a hawk and defends to the leg side
gets across his stumps, works it from outside off behind square on the leg side
round the wicket, uses his long reach and gets well forward to defend
beats the outside edge
oh, another ripper, turn and bounce this time as Broad is beaten again
dropped in a touch short, allows him to defend on the back foot
drops this square into the off side...Broad tells him to stay where he is
slower ball, on off stump, carefully defended
short ball outside off, left alone
comes forward and drives a full delivery just to the left of mid-off
bouncer outside leg stump, Broad ducks
another bouncer, and he'd already had his quota so this is called a no-ball. No free hit, though
full outside off, a flowing cover drive which goes wide of the cover sweeper
short of a length, worked into the leg side
round the wicket, punched firmly towards mid-on
swing and a miss outside off, Broad trying to finish it as Sammy offered up width
another shambolic piece of cricket! An ugly heave to leg, Broad wanted a run but it went straight to square leg. Then Smith hurled his throw way past the stumps. Broad left sprawling in the dirt.
can't beat the field again, pulls a length delivery to Smith at square leg
three in a row, picks out Smith again...lot of effort for no reward as he heaves at a length delivery
full at the stumps, clipped to midwicket
width outside off, driven square into the off side to level the scores
drives at fresh air, not really getting to the pitch
drives firmly but straight to cover
that's the game! Broad slams a drive through the covers and punches the air
